  [1mCrash Location[22m: [38;2;177;185;249mdemo-buggy.c:26:30[39m in the [38;2;177;185;249madd_score[39m function[1mCrash Type[22m:
  [38;2;177;185;249mEXC_BAD_ACCESS (code=1, address=0x0)[39m - segmentation fault due to NULL
  pointer dereference

  [1mRoot Cause[22m:
  1. In the [38;2;177;185;249mcreate_student[39m function ([38;2;177;185;249mdemo-buggy.c:19[39m), the [38;2;177;185;249mscores[39m field is
  intentionally set to [38;2;177;185;249mNULL[39m instead of allocating memory
  2. When [38;2;177;185;249madd_score[39m is called ([38;2;177;185;249mdemo-buggy.c:56[39m), it attempts to write to
  [38;2;177;185;249ms->scores[s->num_scores][39m
  3. Since [38;2;177;185;249ms->scores[39m is [38;2;177;185;249mNULL[39m (address 0x0), this results in a write to
  memory address 0x0, causing a segmentation fault

  [1mVariable State at Crash[22m:
  - [38;2;177;185;249ms[39m (Student pointer): [38;2;177;185;249m0x0000000143605580[39m (valid)
  - [38;2;177;185;249ms->name[39m: [38;2;177;185;249m0x00000001436055a0 "Alice"[39m (valid)
  - [38;2;177;185;249ms->age[39m: [38;2;177;185;249m20[39m (valid)
  - [38;2;177;185;249ms->scores[39m: [38;2;177;185;249m0x0000000000000000[39m (NULL - this is the problem)
  - [38;2;177;185;249ms->num_scores[39m: [38;2;177;185;249m0[39m (valid)
  - [38;2;177;185;249mscore[39m: [38;2;177;185;249m95.5[39m (valid parameter)

  [1mCall Stack[22m:
  1. [38;2;177;185;249mmain[39m at [38;2;177;185;249mdemo-buggy.c:56[39m calls [38;2;177;185;249madd_score(alice, 95.5)[39m
  2. [38;2;177;185;249madd_score[39m at [38;2;177;185;249mdemo-buggy.c:26[39m attempts [38;2;177;185;249ms->scores[s->num_scores] = score[39m
  3. Crash occurs when trying to write to NULL pointer

  The program never reaches the "Adding scores for Bob..." message,
  confirming the crash happens on the first [38;2;177;185;249madd_score[39m call for Alice.
